Date: 15.37 GMT 29 Mar 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Paris AFP (Domestic service) [in French 1537 GMT Thu 29 Mar [edited

France -- New cases of BSE
------------------------------
A total of 5 new cases of bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE) have been
found in the [western departments of Cotes d'Armor, Manche, Orne and
Sarthe, and in the [eastern department of Jura. This makes 50 cases
recorded in France since the beginning of 2001, the Agriculture Ministry
said today, Thu 29 Mar 2001.
